<TEXT>
grand metropolitan plc acquired the pillsbury 
co on sunday 2 months after the british conglomerate started its 
hostile takeover bid for the minneapolisbased food giant the two 
companies announced 
grand met agreed to purchase all outstanding shares of pillsbury 
common stock for 66 per share in cash 3 higher than grand mets 
most recent tender offer which was made last week the total deal 
is worth 568 billion 
the tender offer will expire at midnight jan 3 unless extended 
according to a statement issued by both companies 
pillsbury makes pillsbury flour green giant vegetables and a 
variety of other products and also owns the burger king 
benningans and steak amp ale restaurant chains the company has 
104000 employees during the fiscal year that ended may 31 the 
company had nearly 62 billion in revenues 
the us products and services under the grand met corporate 
umbrella include alpo pet foods pearle vision centres and jampb 
scotch among the british concerns run by the conglomerate are 
gambling casinos 
karl cambronne a lawyer for a group of dissident shareholders 
who sued to have pillsburys poison pill defense against 
takeovers invalidated called the buyout news just wonderful i 
think the shareholders did well 
just friday judges in two states issued key rulings that 
bolstered grand mets bid by weakening pillsburys antitakeover 
efforts 
on oct 3 the day before grand met launched its 60pershare 
bid pillsbury stock was trading at 39 per share on oct 4 after 
the bid was announced it rose to 57 on friday the stock closed 
at 62 
any shares not purchased in the tender offer will be acquired by 
grand met in a subsequent merger at the same 66pershare cash 
price according to the statement 
the boards of both companies approved the offer sunday the 
statement said 
the takeover of pillsbury giant comes less than a month after 
another giant of the industry rjr nabisco agreed to be taken over 
in a leveraged buyout the 25 billion deal was the largest in us 
corporate history 
the offer for pillsbury is conditioned upon a number of things 
among them that there be tendered a number of pillsbury shares that 
would represent at least a majority of the total fully diluted 
shares outstanding according to the statement 
as of the close of business on friday 61848918 of pillsbury 
common shares representing about 724 percent of the companys 
outstanding shares had been tendered to grand met and not withdrawn 
the pillsbury board determined that the terms of the offer and 
the merger were fair and in the best interests of pillsbury 
stockholders the statement said the board also recommended that 
pillsbury stockholders accept the offer and tender their shares 
we are pleased that we have succeeded in protecting the 
interests of our shareholders employees franchisees and 
communities and that we have reached a negotiated agreement that 
works to the advantage of everyone philip l smith chairman and 
chief executive officer of pillsbury said in a statement 
ian a martin chief executive of grand mets us operations 
said grand met officials also are pleased with the agreement 
pillsbury is the perfect fit to enable grand metropolitan to 
achieve its strategy of becoming a world leader in foods and 
retailing as well as the drinks sector martin said our 
company has the resources and expertise to grasp this opportunity 
pillsbury foods and burger king will play a vital role in helping us 
to realize these objectives 
the merger will greatly expand grand metropolitans established 
presence in the huge us marketplace while enabling us to open new 
business opportunities for pillsbury in global markets 
lawyers for pillsbury some of its shareholders and grand met met 
for nearly three hours saturday with a judge but all parties 
refused to comment on the closed meeting 
the meeting came the day after grand met won a major battle in 
its fight for pillsbury 
justice william duffy of the court of chancery in wilmington 
del said friday he would issue preliminary injunctions sought by 
grand met to invalidate pillsburys poison pill takeover defense 
and temporarily block the companys planned spinoff of burger king 
ruling in a separate lawsuit filed in minnesota by dissident 
pillsbury shareholders hennepin county district judge thomas carey 
on friday also temporarily blocked the burger king spinoff and said 
he probably would side with duffy on the poison pill issue 
grand met had asked for the pills removal so it could proceed 
with its tender offer which was 63 a share at that time 
</TEXT>
