<TEXT>
a newspaper reported saturday that 
cuban president fidel castro will come to the inauguration of 
presidentelect carlos andres perez in his first visit to venezuela 
in nearly 30 years 
citing an unidentified aide to perez the newspaper el nacional 
said castro accepted an invitation to the inauguration scheduled 
for feb 2 it said he will travel to venezuela that day 
government spokesmen gave no official confirmation of the report 
perez won the presidential election on dec 4 becoming the first 
venezuelan president to be reelected to office he served his first 
term from 19741979 
he has said one of his first goals is to reestablish diplomatic 
ties with cuba cuba is a latin american nation what happens in 
cuba affects us all perez said in his first official press 
conference thursday 
the two countries severed relations in 1980 over the caracas 
trial of cuban dissident orlando bosch although they have 
maintained sporadic contact since then 
bosch was acquitted three times in venezuela of planning a bomb 
attack on a cuban jetliner in 1976 that killed 73 people he was 
also convicted in the united states in 1976 of a bazooka attack on a 
polish ship that had left cuba 
he later returned to the united states and is being held in 
federal prison near miami pending deportation proceedings 
the cuban leader visited venezuela in 1959 shortly after he took 
power in cuba venezuela had just elected its first president 
romulo betancourt who succeeded ousted strongman gen marcos perez 
jimenez 
relations between cuba and venezuela were strained in the 1960s 
while betancourt struggled to crush a castrobacked guerrilla 
insurgency that threatened venezuelas infant democracy 
in august castro traveled to quito ecuador in his first visit 
to south america in 17 years 
</TEXT>
