<TEXT>
a twa jetliner with only a flight crew 
aboard lost part of its right wing and made an emergency landing 
saturday at kansas city international airport officials said 
the boeing 747 was being flown to chicago by a threemember 
cockpit crew 
it landed safely at the kansas city airport at 348 pm about 
an hour after it left the airport said sandra campbell a 
spokeswoman for the federal aviation administration 
no one was injured 
trans world airlines spokesman don morrison said a 4by8 section 
of the wings metal fabric covering was missing the boeing 747 has 
a wing span of about 195 feet 
it was not a major problem there were no passengers on board 
there wasnt anything of an emergency nature about it said 
morrison from st louis early sunday 
the aircraft was about 100 miles from the airport when the pilot 
noticed part of the wing was gone and requested clearance for the 
emergency return 
officials said they did not know what caused part of the wing to 
fall off 
apparently the crew had no idea how or why it happened 
campbell said the pilot just noticed that part of the wing was 
gone 
depending on the extent of the damage the pilot can compensate 
for it apparently that was the case here because there were no 
serious problems with the landing she said 
