conflictofinterest standards 
he also said all blind trusts for government officials should be 
managed by institutions rather than individuals 
gray said bush also would consider the white house as one entity 
for purposes of postemployment lobbying restrictions rather than 
precluding people from lobbying only the section of the executive 
branch where they worked 
the compartmentalization of the executive office of the 
president i think is something the vice president thinks is 
somewhat artificial and ought to go gray said because they 
interact on such a daily basis 
in other words a person would be barred from lobbying not only 
the part of the white house where he or she worked such as the 
office of management and budget national security council or office 
of the vice president but would be restricted in contacts from all 
white house sections 
