<TEXT>
communist party leader zhao ziyang on sunday 
marked the 10th anniversary of a historic meeting that ushered in 
chinas economic reforms by saying the current crisis in marxism 
offers new opportunities 
china is advancing and the world is changing zhao told about 
400 scholars and party officials at a symposium honoring a major 
central committee meeting held dec 1822 1978 
numerous problems are arising which call for answers to them 
some people say this has posed a crisis for marxism yet in fact 
for marxism challenges mean new opportunities for development 
the official xinhua news agency quoted zhao as saying 
celebrations of the anniversary have been subdued as a result of 
chinas worst economic crisis since deng xiaoping took control in 
1978 following the death in 1976 of chairman mao tsetung 
in september the government called for a prolonged economic 
slowdown including a pullback on some reforms to cope with an 
inflation rate officially set at 26 percent excessive government 
spending and a breakdown of financial controls 
zhao told the symposium that china must closely examine present 
conditions and learn from practice to develop marxist theory he 
stressed the idea that the country will be in a primary stage of 
socialism for the next century and its main task is to advance the 
productive forces 
the 1978 meeting is regarded as a turning point in chinese 
history deng a pragmatist who emerged as chinas leader 
introduced his reforms at the meeting he called for reorganizing 
the economy such as breaking up communes in favor of family 
farming and encouraging private initiative and marketoriented 
economic principles he also made clear that economic development 
not class struggle was chinas top priority 
in the past decade dengs reforms have doubled chinas gross 
national product and more than doubled personal incomes 
but the official guangming daily in an editorial on the 
anniversary said the tendency to try to achieve too much at one 
time has caused policy makers to stray from the seeking truth from 
facts concept emphasized by deng at the 1978 meeting 
they are problems in the process of advance and progress and so 
long as we stick to the principles adopted at the historical plenum 
we can overcome all these problems 
</TEXT>
