aviation border trade and science and technology consular offices 
in the chinese city of shanghai and the indian city of bombay may 
also be established as a result 
however little progress is expected on the main issue dividing 
the two countries their 2400milelong border they fought a brief 
border war in 1962 and china occupied about 15000 square miles of 
indian territory that india still wants back 
the two countries began border talks in 1981 but made little 
progress in eight rounds 
india was one of the first nonsocialist countries to recognize 
communist china soon after chinas 1949 revolution 
