leader mao tsetung and prime minister nehru 
in the late 1970s relations improved slightly when china began 
emphasizing traditional statetostate relations instead of 
exporting communist revolution 
both chinese and indian officials say gandhis visit is intended 
to create an atmosphere for greater communication not resolve the 
border question 
